  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "A horticultural and pharmaceutical writer who was
        admired for completing Virgil (Serv. Georg. 4,148). He lived in the 3rd cent. AD (SHA Alex.
        37,9) ....The work (De hortis ?) was together with the Roman agronomists part of the
        Florentine Cod. Marcianus but had already been removed from this collection before the codex
        was completely lost in the 16th cent.... Parts are preserved in Palladius' books of the
        months under the headings De hortis and De pomis; the Neapolitan Fr. De arboribus pomiferis
        (pom.) of the 6th cent. (on quince, peach, almond, chestnut) as well as reworkings and
        excerpts, especially the Medicinae ex oleribus et pomis (med.), contain more material.
        Important sources for G. were Pliny, Celsus and Columella. The curae boum ex corpore Gargili
        Martialis are now considered forgeries on linguistic grounds...." Christmann, Eckhard
        (Heidelberg) Gargilius." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and ;
        Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2010. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 01 October 2010 </mads:note>
